<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="156">
1. 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:230024" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Macromeris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uploaded - Macromeris iridipennis" lsidName-HNS="Macromeris iridipennis" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iridipennis">Macromeris iridipennis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="156">M. caeruleo-nigra; abdomine iridescente, alis caeruleo-violaceoque splendide micantibus; pedibus mutieis, simplicibus.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="156">Female. Length 12 lines. Blue-black; abdomen with a changeable iridescent pile; head and thorax with a black velvety pubescence; the metathorax very finely rugose and opake; the legs simple; the posterior tibiae villose within; the wings very dark brown, with a splendid violet and blue iridescence.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="156">Male. Very closely resembling the female, but rather smaller; the anterior and intermediate femora more incrassate, and all the femora with a simple row of teeth or serrations on their inferior margins.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageNumber="156">
Hab. 
<collectingRegion country="Indonesia" pageNumber="156">Aru</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="156">
Although this species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:127754" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Macromeris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Macromeris Lepeletier" lsidName-HNS="Macromeris Lepeletier" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Macromeris</taxonomicName>
is very similar in colour to the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:230025" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Macromeris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uploaded - Macromeris violacea" lsidName-HNS="Macromeris violacea" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="violacea">M. violacea</taxonomicName>
of St. - Fargeau, the femora are not so thick as in that species, not in fact much more so than in the female; and the row of teeth beneath is a strong specific character.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
